00:41:22,400 --> 00:41:23,159
If the Princess Royal

839
00:41:24,079 --> 00:41:25,480
are you suspecting me of
framing this young man up

840
00:41:25,480 --> 00:41:28,199
at the cost of my teacher's reputation?

841
00:41:28,760 --> 00:41:29,320
I dare not.

842
00:41:30,239 --> 00:41:32,320
It's just that unlike Beiqi,

843
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:34,599
Nanqing emphasizes laws.

844
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:37,480
If you want to accuse someone,

845
00:41:38,239 --> 00:41:39,360
words alone

846
00:41:39,800 --> 00:41:41,119
won't be enough.

847
00:41:43,880 --> 00:41:46,079
Your Highness, you've made a point.

848
00:41:53,280 --> 00:41:56,079
Look, it was written by my teacher

849
00:41:56,079 --> 00:41:57,320
back then.

850
00:42:00,320 --> 00:42:01,679
Could it be

851
00:42:02,119 --> 00:42:03,280
the proof?

852
00:42:18,159 --> 00:42:19,800
The lines are exactly the same.

853
00:42:41,159 --> 00:42:45,039
Even without the handwritten copy,

854
00:42:46,400 --> 00:42:47,920
we can see the truth.

855
00:42:50,039 --> 00:42:51,599
The latter four lines of the poem

856
00:42:52,800 --> 00:42:53,960
depict a desolated

857
00:42:54,639 --> 00:42:56,199
and frustrated life.

858
00:42:57,519 --> 00:42:59,480
Without going through

859
00:42:59,960 --> 00:43:01,280
ups and downs in life,

860
00:43:02,360 --> 00:43:04,960
how could anyone ever depict
such an artistic conception?

861
00:43:06,760 --> 00:43:07,800
But Mr. Fan,

862
00:43:08,239 --> 00:43:09,679
you're successful and famous
at a young age.

863
00:43:10,800 --> 00:43:12,800
How could you be so sad

864
00:43:12,800 --> 00:43:14,159
and desolated?

865
00:43:17,079 --> 00:43:19,039
When a young man
tries to express sorrow,

866
00:43:20,920 --> 00:43:22,599
he would normally go too far.

867
00:43:35,239 --> 00:43:35,800
Your Majesty.

868
00:43:41,960 --> 00:43:42,400
Your Majesty.

869
00:43:42,760 --> 00:43:44,320
Fan Xian gains a reputation
by deception.

870
00:43:44,960 --> 00:43:46,039
He's utterly shameless.

871
00:43:46,679 --> 00:43:47,840
By doing so,

872
00:43:48,039 --> 00:43:49,760
he has disgraced

873
00:43:49,760 --> 00:43:50,599
all the scholars of Nanqing.

874
00:43:50,719 --> 00:43:51,639
I beg Your Majesty to

875
00:43:52,039 --> 00:43:53,599
deprive him of his official title,

876
00:43:53,719 --> 00:43:54,599
expel him from the capital city,

877
00:43:54,800 --> 00:43:56,880
and never recruit him
as an official again.

878
00:43:57,920 --> 00:43:58,480
Young Master Guo!

879
00:43:59,159 --> 00:44:00,119
Since I've disgraced

880
00:44:00,119 --> 00:44:01,159
Nanqing,

881
00:44:01,360 --> 00:44:03,039
why are you so happy?

882
00:44:03,719 --> 00:44:04,400
Nonsense!

883
00:44:05,920 --> 00:44:06,960
I'm just furious.

884
00:44:07,719 --> 00:44:09,559
I feel ashamed to be your colleague.

885
00:44:09,960 --> 00:44:11,760
When did you know that Master Zhuang

886
00:44:11,880 --> 00:44:13,159
would argue about the truth on the Hall?

887
00:44:22,159 --> 00:44:23,400
I just heard him of course.

888
00:44:23,679 --> 00:44:24,800
Then why did you say with certainty that

889
00:44:24,800 --> 00:44:25,920
I would be utterly discredited

890
00:44:25,920 --> 00:44:27,320
the moment I arrived at

891
00:44:27,320 --> 00:44:29,119
the Hall of Prayer for Good Harvest?

892
00:44:29,519 --> 00:44:31,199
Either you're good at fortune-telling,

893
00:44:31,400 --> 00:44:32,800
or you've hooked up with Master Zhuang

894
00:44:32,800 --> 00:44:34,039
in advance!

895
00:44:34,480 --> 00:44:35,480
Nonsense!

896
00:44:37,599 --> 00:44:38,239
How could you use "hook up" to describe

897
00:44:38,239 --> 00:44:39,119
my relationship with Master Zhuang?

898
00:44:39,559 --> 00:44:40,119
Well,

899
00:44:40,880 --> 00:44:41,719
At such a critical moment,

900
00:44:42,159 --> 00:44:43,360
just forget about the choice of words.

901
00:44:49,000 --> 00:44:49,519
Your Majesty,

902
00:44:50,159 --> 00:44:52,519
my son doesn't get along with Fan Xian
all the time.

903
00:44:53,119 --> 00:44:55,719
Their dispute matters nothing.

904
00:44:56,159 --> 00:44:57,320
What's important now

905
00:44:57,960 --> 00:44:59,480
is Fan Xian's poem.

906
00:44:59,639 --> 00:45:01,519
Since he copied other's work,

907
00:45:01,719 --> 00:45:03,079
he should be severely punished,

908
00:45:03,519 --> 00:45:06,400
or the public anger

909
00:45:06,840 --> 00:45:08,440
won't be quelled.

910
00:45:10,239 --> 00:45:11,760
Minister, good for you.

911
00:45:11,760 --> 00:45:13,079
You pointed out the heart of
the matter directly.

912
00:45:14,480 --> 00:45:16,159
I just spoke my mind impartially.

913
00:45:16,880 --> 00:45:17,639
Master Zhuang,

914
00:45:19,719 --> 00:45:20,920
you're right.

915
00:45:21,800 --> 00:45:24,920
I copied that poem from others.

916
00:45:26,559 --> 00:45:27,880
He really copied from other's work!

917
00:45:33,800 --> 00:45:34,440
Mr. Fan,

918
00:45:37,000 --> 00:45:40,159
you're brave to admit your mistake.

919
00:45:41,360 --> 00:45:43,199
After this, you're sure

920
00:45:43,880 --> 00:45:45,079
to achieve great success in future.

921
00:45:45,880 --> 00:45:47,719
Stop flattering me.

922
00:45:49,039 --> 00:45:49,920
Master Zhuang,

923
00:45:50,920 --> 00:45:52,559
I copied poem for myself,

924
00:45:53,000 --> 00:45:54,519
and you copied poem for your teacher.

925
00:45:54,519 --> 00:45:56,400
We're no different.

926
00:45:56,679 --> 00:45:57,159
In fact,

927
00:45:57,159 --> 00:45:58,840
you're not as frank as I am.

928
00:46:00,119 --> 00:46:01,119
This poem

929
00:46:01,440 --> 00:46:02,920
is written by Du Fu, the Saint of Poem,

930
00:46:02,920 --> 00:46:04,239
who is also known as Shaoling Yelao.

931
00:46:04,519 --> 00:46:06,400
It has nothing to do with your teacher.

932
00:46:08,239 --> 00:46:11,280
Gaining fame for your teacher
by deceiving the public,

933
00:46:12,280 --> 00:46:15,400
Master Zhuang is really a role model
of respecting teacher and honoring truth.

934
00:46:15,920 --> 00:46:16,800
The Saint of Poem?

935
00:46:20,320 --> 00:46:22,360
Which dynasty

936
00:46:22,840 --> 00:46:24,760
was he from?

937
00:46:25,320 --> 00:46:26,360
As the Saint of Poem,

938
00:46:26,880 --> 00:46:28,840
did he go down in history?

939
00:46:29,480 --> 00:46:30,880
We can't find him in historical records.

940
00:46:32,719 --> 00:46:33,719
I see.

941
00:46:34,199 --> 00:46:35,280
Because his poems

942
00:46:36,280 --> 00:46:37,920
are from another world.

943
00:46:38,960 --> 00:46:40,719
A world lasts for thousands of years

944
00:46:40,880 --> 00:46:42,440
and is filled with splendid poems.

945
00:46:44,360 --> 00:46:45,400
Is it the fairyland

946
00:46:47,079 --> 00:46:49,199
existed in legends?

947
00:46:52,920 --> 00:46:55,920
Feel free to laugh! Feel free to laugh!

948
00:46:56,639 --> 00:46:58,239
It's definitely the fairyland

949
00:46:59,280 --> 00:47:02,119
compared to your world.

950
00:47:03,280 --> 00:47:04,400
Have you been there?

951
00:47:06,679 --> 00:47:08,719
It's a picture scroll
left from my dream,

952
00:47:10,480 --> 00:47:11,960
a memory left in my head.

953
00:47:12,159 --> 00:47:13,000
Your Excellency Fan,

954
00:47:13,800 --> 00:47:15,119
you mean

955
00:47:15,760 --> 00:47:18,239
you've travelled to the fairyland

956
00:47:19,480 --> 00:47:20,719
and recited a poem in your dream.

957
00:47:30,800 --> 00:47:31,360
Your Majesty.

958
00:47:32,039 --> 00:47:33,159
what Fan Xian said

959
00:47:33,760 --> 00:47:35,519
is utterly ridiculous.

960
00:47:37,320 --> 00:47:39,679
By making up such an absurd story,
he lied to Your Majesty.

961
00:47:40,280 --> 00:47:41,960
Your Majesty, I beg you to punish him!

962
00:47:46,199 --> 00:47:47,079
Master Zhuang,

963
00:47:48,039 --> 00:47:49,719
has your teacher written a lot of poems?

964
00:47:50,880 --> 00:47:53,599
My teacher has written
many excellent poems.

965
00:47:54,559 --> 00:47:57,880
Does he have many unpublished poems?

966
00:47:59,360 --> 00:48:01,039
I've gone through all his works,

967
00:48:01,920 --> 00:48:03,119
and that is the only poem

968
00:48:03,800 --> 00:48:06,360
that remains unpublished.

969
00:48:13,119 --> 00:48:17,559
Who told you
I only recited one poem in my dream?

970
00:48:24,920 --> 00:48:25,760
Give me paper.

971
00:48:27,360 --> 00:48:28,159
Give me ink.

972
00:48:30,039 --> 00:48:30,760
Mr. Fan,

973
00:48:31,400 --> 00:48:32,559
if you want to compose poems,

974
00:48:32,880 --> 00:48:35,280
I'd like to write them down for you.

975
00:48:40,360 --> 00:48:42,320
You want to

976
00:48:42,320 --> 00:48:44,119
improvise more poems

977
00:48:44,840 --> 00:48:47,400
to prove that you saw them all

978
00:48:47,400 --> 00:48:48,320
from the fairyland?

979
00:48:50,079 --> 00:48:51,119
you don't know

980
00:48:51,880 --> 00:48:53,079
That memory

981
00:48:54,159 --> 00:48:56,280
is literally carved

982
00:48:56,280 --> 00:48:57,719
into my head.

983
00:48:57,960 --> 00:49:00,280
Every word I saw

984
00:49:00,840 --> 00:49:02,480
and every book I read,

985
00:49:03,239 --> 00:49:04,840
I can remember them clearly

986
00:49:05,360 --> 00:49:06,320
as if they're right in front of me.

987
00:49:08,079 --> 00:49:09,920
Do you know what you're talking about?

988
00:49:11,280 --> 00:49:12,800
I'm afraid he's so exasperated that

989
00:49:12,800 --> 00:49:14,559
he starts to talk nonsense.

990
00:49:24,920 --> 00:49:28,239
Don't you see
the Yellow River pouring from heaven,

991
00:49:29,840 --> 00:49:33,119
rushing to the sea, never to return?

992
00:49:34,800 --> 00:49:39,920
Don't you see, in the hall
the mirror is saddened by the grey hair?

993
00:49:41,039 --> 00:49:45,239
Young and dark at dawn,
but at dusk snowy!

994
00:49:45,960 --> 00:49:49,239
Ah, let's enjoy ourselves while we can.

995
00:49:50,039 --> 00:49:53,079
"It's wrong to set goblets idle,
in the glory of the moon."

996
00:49:54,679 --> 00:49:58,800
I was created by Heaven,
certainly not for nothing.

997
00:50:00,360 --> 00:50:03,800
As for money,
it scatters and gathers as money should.

998
00:50:10,239 --> 00:50:13,039
When will there be no more
moon and spring flowers?

999
00:50:13,920 --> 00:50:15,880
For me who had so many memorable hours?

1000
00:50:17,920 --> 00:50:21,000
If youask me
how much my sorrow has increased,

1001
00:50:21,559 --> 00:50:26,119
just see the overbrimming river
flowing east!

1002
00:50:28,119 --> 00:50:30,079
I do not know in the celestial sphere.

1003
00:50:30,960 --> 00:50:33,159
what name this festive night goes by?

1004
00:50:33,360 --> 00:50:36,280
I want to fly home, riding the air,

1005
00:50:37,559 --> 00:50:40,559
but fear the ethereal cold up there.

1006
00:50:41,039 --> 00:50:43,239
The jade and crystal mansions are so high!
[*It's too high and too cold for me.]

1007
00:50:43,760 --> 00:50:46,199
Dancing to my shadow,

1008
00:50:46,480 --> 00:50:49,760
I feel no longer the mortal tie.

1009
00:50:50,960 --> 00:50:53,519
Though drunk,
we lit the lamp to see the glaive.

1010
00:50:54,519 --> 00:50:57,280
Sober, we heard the horns
from tent to tent.

1011
00:50:59,000 --> 00:51:01,119
Under the flags, beef grilled was eaten
by our warriors brave.

1012
00:51:01,440 --> 00:51:03,880
And martial airs were played
by fifty instruments.

1013
00:51:04,480 --> 00:51:07,000
It was an autumn maneuver in the field.

1014
00:51:15,719 --> 00:51:19,719
We wished to fly in heaven,
two birds with the wings of one,

1015
00:51:20,960 --> 00:51:24,199
and to grow together on the earth,
two branches of one tree.

1016
00:51:24,679 --> 00:51:27,440
On the road ahead
surely will be friends dear and true.

1017
00:51:28,719 --> 00:51:32,280
Throughout the land is there anyone
who knows not you?

1018
00:51:33,440 --> 00:51:36,119
My attic which last night
in vernal wind did stand.

1019
00:51:37,599 --> 00:51:39,639
A few plum twigs
at the corner of the wall

1020
00:51:40,079 --> 00:51:41,840
blossoming all alone, defying the cold!

1021
00:51:41,840 --> 00:51:43,960
Would you have me bow my head
before mighty princes?

1022
00:51:44,360 --> 00:51:46,360
On war-torn land streams flow
and mountains stand.

1023
00:51:46,719 --> 00:51:48,800
In vernal town grass
and weeds are overgrown.

1024
00:51:49,320 --> 00:51:51,280
Though I am white-haired,
still I'd sing and drink my fill.

1025
00:51:52,920 --> 00:51:56,880
Hating to part,
hearing birds breaks our heart.

1026
00:51:57,000 --> 00:51:59,679
We can't fly wing to wing
like a pair of phoenixes,

1027
00:52:00,239 --> 00:52:03,480
yet our hearts closely linked
beat in harmony.

1028
00:52:03,679 --> 00:52:06,679
Here's my precious horse,
here's my priceless fur.

1029
00:52:06,800 --> 00:52:09,679
Tell the boy to give them for the wine.

1030
00:52:10,559 --> 00:52:13,280
I want to fly home, riding the air,

1031
00:52:14,400 --> 00:52:17,440
but fear the ethereal cold up there.

1032
00:52:18,320 --> 00:52:22,239
Hear spring rain
falling in a small mansionall night!

1033
00:52:22,239 --> 00:52:24,519
Till mountains crumble, streams run dry,

1034
00:52:24,519 --> 00:52:26,400
thunder rumbles in winter,
snow falls in summer.

1035
00:52:26,400 --> 00:52:29,559
West of the Yangguan Pass
you'll see no more of mine.

1036
00:52:29,559 --> 00:52:31,079
I do not know in the celestial sphere.

1037
00:52:31,079 --> 00:52:32,760
Men are born sentimental and emotional.

1038
00:52:32,760 --> 00:52:34,039
Myriad footpaths
with no human traces shown.

1039
00:52:34,519 --> 00:52:36,000
For the long years,

1040
00:52:36,760 --> 00:52:39,960
to whom can I my grief convey?

1041
00:52:39,960 --> 00:52:42,480
Youth do not know real depression.

1042
00:52:43,840 --> 00:52:45,920
Time passes indifferently,
turning people from young to old.

1043
00:52:47,719 --> 00:52:51,440
Revived even if she be,
could she still know me?

1044
00:52:51,920 --> 00:52:54,800
Near a cottage a stream flows.

1045
00:52:56,880 --> 00:52:59,199
How panic-stricken I was retreating
before the Tartars!

1046
00:53:00,639 --> 00:53:02,760
Being a captive,
I lamented over my solitary confinement.

1047
00:53:04,000 --> 00:53:07,000
Who can avert his death
since time immemorial?

1048
00:53:08,360 --> 00:53:13,119
Let my heart remain true to
shine in the annals.

1049
00:53:20,639 --> 00:53:23,039
No ancients before me,

1050
00:53:25,199 --> 00:53:27,559
nor comers from behind.

1051
00:53:32,039 --> 00:53:34,679
Reflecting on
the infinite heaven and earth,

1052
00:53:38,199 --> 00:53:41,119
Alone, in a sadness sublime,
my tears come.

1053
00:53:55,519 --> 00:53:56,599
Is it over one hundred?

1054
00:53:57,719 --> 00:54:00,480
Mr. Fan, it's way over one hundred.

1055
00:54:01,400 --> 00:54:02,559
That'll be enough.

1056
00:54:03,320 --> 00:54:06,440
How could there be any fairyland
in the world?

1057
00:54:07,559 --> 00:54:08,519
If not,

1058
00:54:08,519 --> 00:54:09,119
where do all these poems

1059
00:54:09,119 --> 00:54:10,360
come from?

1060
00:54:10,440 --> 00:54:13,400
They must be written by himself!

1061
00:54:18,360 --> 00:54:19,800
Even if

1062
00:54:19,800 --> 00:54:21,079
he writes them all,

1063
00:54:22,239 --> 00:54:24,960
even if he writes thousands of poems,

1064
00:54:25,440 --> 00:54:26,800
it can't prove that

1065
00:54:27,280 --> 00:54:30,039
he didn't copy that poem.

1066
00:54:30,440 --> 00:54:32,519
He can recite marvelous poems
without thinking.

1067
00:54:33,239 --> 00:54:34,199
how could he

1068
00:54:34,679 --> 00:54:35,800
copy other's work?

1069
00:54:36,840 --> 00:54:38,079
Why should he?

1070
00:54:44,920 --> 00:54:46,639
When it comes to explaining
classic texts and annotating articles,

1071
00:54:47,960 --> 00:54:49,239
you win.

1072
00:54:51,000 --> 00:54:51,800
But when it comes to reciting poems,

1073
00:54:53,159 --> 00:54:54,599
I win.

1074
00:54:56,639 --> 00:54:58,360
For a literary giant...

1075
00:55:00,239 --> 00:55:01,639
...I'm not qualified.

1076
00:55:04,199 --> 00:55:05,320
But for a man,

1077
00:55:07,679 --> 00:55:10,840
you're not qualified.

1078
00:55:19,840 --> 00:55:24,239
Since I am drunk and sleepy,
you may go...

1079
00:55:34,760 --> 00:55:36,239
What's wrong, Master Zhuang?

1080
00:55:36,639 --> 00:55:37,559
What's wrong, Master Zhuang?

1081
00:55:37,920 --> 00:55:42,480
Master Zhuang!

1082
00:55:42,760 --> 00:55:44,199
Master Zhuang, wake up!

1083
00:55:46,519 --> 00:55:47,639
Get the imperial physician!

1084
00:55:55,840 --> 00:55:56,400
Hurry! Hurry! Hurry!

1085
00:55:57,239 --> 00:55:59,079
Come on.
Put the sober soup on the table.

1086
00:56:00,119 --> 00:56:01,280
Put it here! Put it here! Right!

1087
00:56:01,760 --> 00:56:02,400
Plump the pillow

1088
00:56:02,400 --> 00:56:03,320
to make it soft.

1089
00:56:04,599 --> 00:56:05,519
He drank too much.

1090
00:56:05,519 --> 00:56:06,440
Make sure
he won't get a stiff neck tomorrow.

1091
00:56:10,400 --> 00:56:13,000
The plan remains unchanged.
Wait for me outside the palace walls.

1092
00:56:13,360 --> 00:56:14,039
No!

1093
00:56:14,039 --> 00:56:15,280
You're so drunk.

1094
00:56:15,280 --> 00:56:16,000
Let's make it another day.

1095
00:56:17,440 --> 00:56:18,079
He's here! He's here!

1096
00:56:18,079 --> 00:56:19,079
Mr. Fan, the poetic genius, is here!

1097
00:56:19,400 --> 00:56:20,440
You're here! Hurry up!

1098
00:56:20,719 --> 00:56:21,920
Put him on the bed! Put him on the bed!

1099
00:56:22,199 --> 00:56:23,039
Be careful! Be careful!

1100
00:56:28,320 --> 00:56:28,840
Slow down!

1101
00:56:30,400 --> 00:56:30,920
Cover him up!

1102
00:56:31,639 --> 00:56:32,159
Hurry! Hurry! Hurry!

1103
00:56:34,760 --> 00:56:36,800
Be careful! Cover him up!

1104
00:56:39,360 --> 00:56:40,079
